content:
A chat transcript is a record of a chat between a customer and an agent. Salesforce automatically creates a transcript for each chat session.

Available in: Salesforce Classic, Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. To avoid service interruptions, migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

When a chat ends successfully, the transcript is created as soon as the agent closes the chat window. You can associate a transcript with cases, accounts, contacts, and leads, or link it to other objects.

You can create, view, edit, or delete chat transcripts if you have the correct permissions. However, we don't recommend tampering with these records in most cases.

To be transparent with customers, display an auto-greeting that explains what happens to chat transcripts. This article isn't legal advice; consult your legal counsel for compliance considerations.

Chat transcript fields help track information about agents' chats with customers. Live chat transcript events automatically track events between agents and customers during chats.
title: Understanding Chat Transcripts in Service Cloud
